y growing fulfillment of the inner commandments. With an integrative approach that puts Baḥya in dialogue with other medieval Muslim and Jewish religious thinkers, this work offers a fresh perspective on our understanding of the interconnectedness of the dynamic, neighboring religious traditions of Judaism and Islam. Contributing to conversations in the history of religion, Jewish studies, and medieval studies on interiority and mysticism, this book reveals Baḥya as a revolutionary and demanding thinker of Jewish law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCommandments (Judaism)xEarly works to 1800. 0aIslamxRelationsxJudaism. 0aJewish ethics. 0aJewish lawxEarly works to 1800. 0aJudaismxRelationsxIslam. 0aMysticismxJudaism. 0aPhilosophy, Medieval. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Theology.2bisacsh  aComparative Religion.  aHalakhah/Jewish Law.  aInteriority.  aInterreligious Dynamics.  aJewish Philosophy.  aJewish-Muslim Relations.  aJudeo-Arabic Literature.  aMedieval Studies.  aPiety.  aSubjectivity.  aTheology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079132740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363746740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503637467423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503637467/original  a978-3-11-079132-7  Stanford University Press